The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. Concurrent medical conditions included Parkinson's disease, Drug allergy (penicillin) and Drug allergy (ampicillin). Concomitant products included CEFALEXIN, CARBIDOPA, SILDENAFIL (VIAGRA [SILDENAFIL]) and DILTIAZEM for an unknown indication. On 14-Mar-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. ADVERSE EVENT REPORT: MODERNA VACCINE 1 of 2 Dates: Feb. 17 to March 16, 2021 1. I received the first dose of the Moderna Anti-COVID19 vaccine at the Outpatient Clinic on Feb. 17, 2021 at 1:31PM. I have been suffering from Gulf War Illness (GWI) for over four years. a. My condition is a combination of ME/CFS and Fibromyalgia. Please review these CDC pages for details: https://www.cdc.gov/me-cfs/index.html and https://www.cdc.gov/arthritis/basics/fibromyalgia.htm. b. GWI a neuro-immunologic disease that is still not well understood by the medical community. 2. Feb. 17, 2021. I received the FIRST MODERNA VACCINE SHOT on my right arm on Wednesday, Feb. 17, 2021. The injection site hurt for two days (Feb. 17 & 18, 2021). I had the following side effects on Feb.17, 2021: chills, headache, joint pain (arthralgia), muscle pain (myalgia), fatigue, nausea, and swollen glands. 3. Feb 18, 2021. I had no side effects. 4. Feb. 19, 2021. I had a headache. 5. Feb. 20, 2021. On Saturday, Feb. 20, 2021, I walked one mile in 29 minutes. I felt tired, weak, short of breath, and I had to stop walking on 4 separate occasions. I produced phlegm. The phlegm secretions were white, very thick, and extremely sticky. I started Mucinex 1200MG (guaifenesin) and Neil-Med Saline Solution nose irrigations this day. 6. Feb. 21, 2021. On Monday, Feb. 21, 2021 between 1AM to 7AM, I had itching at the injection site (right arm), chills, headache, arthralgia, myalgia, fatigue, nausea, and swollen neck glands. 7. Feb. 22, 2021. From 8AM to 4PM my side effects were itching at the injection site (right arm), chills, headache, arthralgia, myalgia, fatigue, nausea, swollen neck glands, coughing, and stomachache. At 5PM I had difficulty breathing. It lasted until 8PM. I took albuterol via nebulizer and was observed by my wife and son to ensure that I did not get worse. 8. Feb. 23, 2021. No side effects. 9. Feb. 24, 2021. I had a headache and a runny nose. 10. Feb. 25, 2021. It has been 8 days since I received the first dose of the Moderna COVID19 EUA. The side effects have been chills, cough, shortness of breath (oxygen saturation of 95%), and thick white and sticky phlegm. Today my neck glands and tongue are swollen. My throat, and the inside of my ears hurt. My nose is runny, like if I had a cold, and I sneezing often. My chest congestion has moved from my chest to my nose sinuses. I have no nausea today. I have no fever. My injection site does not hurt. My Rosacea became active today. Today, I wore an N95 mask to ensure that I did get anyone in my family sick. They all wore their N95 masks. At 6:35 PM, I had a Gulf War Illness ?crash? and was bedridden until 9:06 PM. At 9PM both my malaise and nausea were back. 11. Feb 26 to Mar 2, 2021. I had no Moderna vaccine side effects. 12. Mar 3, 2021. I had four explosive vomiting episodes starting at 10AM. Initially, I thought that the vomiting had nothing to do with the Moderna vaccine. However, my son ate the same food that I did and he did not vomit. I vomited so hard that my son wanted to take me to the Emergency Department, but I refused. I vomited four times today Saturday, March 3, 2021. Every time I vomited it sounded horrible to my family members. The vomit had an extraordinarily strong nasty smell. 13. March 4, 2021 to the present. I have not experienced any Moderna vaccine side effects side March 3, 2021. In conclusion, for any questions regarding this Adverse Event Report please email me. Thank you. Very respectfully,

The medical history was not provided. Concomitant product use was not provided. On 07 Jan 2021, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (lot/batch: unknown) intramuscularly in the arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. 65 2021-03-10 injection site pain About 6 hours after vaccination I experienced soreness at the site of the injection (scale of 4-5). ... Read more
Close
About 6 hours after vaccination I experienced soreness at the site of the injection (scale of 4-5). Overnight the pain got worse (scale 6 or more). The pain at the site was more than I have experienced with a tetanus shot. It was uncomfortable to sleep or rollover. The pain was more than I have had with any previous injection. The next morning which is today, I examined the site of the injection and saw that the injection site was at the top of the deltoid muscle approaching the bursar. I am not a large individual at 5' 8" and 140 pounds. My deltoid is not very large and the injection was above the thickest part of the deltoid. I am a pharmacist and give injections, I also had my wife look at it, she is also a injection administering pharmacist. We both determined the injection site was outside the normal injection location of the deltoid. It is now over 24 hours since the injection, and the pain/discomfort is subsiding. At this point the pain is similar to a tetanus shot and acceptable (scale 2-3).

Close
Within 24 hours, I began experiencing bouts of severe pruritis starting in the lower extremities. Rash developed in areas of excoriation due to severe itching, pinpoint red macules. The episodes of pruritis were not responsive to Benadryl Zyrtec or Claritin. For two nights I took Vistaril with mild relief. Medrol dose pack was ineffective. Over the next week the episodes increased in intensity and frequency and were often accompanied by localized redness and superficial swelling of the skin and hive like raised areas of the skin as in urticaria. The areas of localized pruritis migrated over a period lasting 7 to 10 days, first to inner surfaces of both my arms, then to my lower back, and then to my upper back over scapulae and shoulders. Concurrently, the pruritis and rash began resolving in the lower extremities and then on the inner aspect of my upper extremities. Currently, the intensity and frequency of the pruritis has decreased significantly and is now localized to my upper back. Yesterday was the first day that I did not require antihistamines.

On 27 Feb 2021, the patient started getting redness and pain in his left bicep. He had a lymph node about the size of a ping pong formed in his armpit. The patient received both scheduled doses of mRNA-1273 prior to the events; therefore, action taken with the drug in response to the events was not applicable. inflammation of bowels; inflammation of stomach; flu like symptoms; runny nose; local pain; This spontaneous case was reported by a consumer and describes the occurrence of INFLAMMATORY BOWEL DISEASE (inflammation of bowels) in a 67-year-old male patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch nos. 029k20A and 025J20A) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. The patient's past medical history included Cardiac ablation on 27-Jun-2019. Concurrent medical conditions included Atrial fibrillation (resolved with meds and ablation), Blood pressure high and Allergic rhinitis. Concomitant products included ASPIRIN [ACETYLSALICYLIC ACID] for Atrial fibrillation, AMLODIPINE and BISOPROLOL for Blood pressure high, ESOMEPRAZOLE SODIUM (NEXIUM [ESOMEPRAZOLE SODIUM]) for GERD, FENOFIBRATE for Hyperlipidemia, ZOLPIDEM for Insomnia. On 13-Jan-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 12-Feb-2021, received second dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) dosage was changed to 1 dosage form. On 12-Feb-2021, the patient experienced INFLUENZA LIKE ILLNESS (flu like symptoms), RHINORRHOEA (runny nose) and VACCINATION SITE PAIN (local pain). On 13-Feb-2021, the patient experienced INFLAMMATORY BOWEL DISEASE (inflammation of bowels) (seriousness criterion medically significant) and GASTRITIS (inflammation of stomach). On 30-Apr-2021, INFLAMMATORY BOWEL DISEASE (inflammation of bowels) and GASTRITIS (inflammation of stomach) had resolved with sequelae. At the time of the report, INFLUENZA LIKE ILLNESS (flu like symptoms) and VACCINATION SITE PAIN (local pain) had resolved and RHINORRHOEA (runny nose) outcome was unknown. The patient went to their doctor who referred him to a gastrointestinal specialist. The patient had an endoscopy and ABD CT (abdominal computerized tomogram) scan. The patient stated that diverticulitis was suspected. The scans were reported as cleared, and an obstruction was cleared as well. There was inflammation of the stomach and bowels. Additional treatment information was not provided. The patient received both scheduled doses of mRNA-1273 prior to the event(s); therefore, action taken with the drug in response to the event(s) is not applicable. 68 2021-03-05 injection site pain More than normal pain was experiences as the vaccine was being administered. About four hours after ... Read more
Close
More than normal pain was experiences as the vaccine was being administered. About four hours after injection, extreme pain in left shoulder, rotator cuff, unable to move arm . Had to take ibuprofen approximately every six hours for the next 24 hours. Two days since the injection, the pain is about 20 percent less. NOTE 1: The probable reason for the unusual pain was that the injection was given much too high on the arm, near the top of the shoulder. I went back to the pharmacy on March 6, 2021, spoke with senior pharmacist, and showed the injection location with the band-aid still on. He noted it was a "bit high" and who had administered the vaccine. He said he would look into the injection technique of the person who had administered the dose. NOTE 2 - THIS IS THE REASON I SUBMIT THIS REPORT: While the situation is handled at the pharmacy in question, I believe that with the rush to get the vaccine into arms, the CDC may need to pay more attention to the experience level of those administering it, making sure they have the proper training and actually have learned the proper injection technique. The CDC's YouTube video I have seen on the injection technique is a bit long. The segment beginning at the 2:40 minute point should be separated and labeled "injection technique for adults" and have it made clearer that the injection is at the CENTER of the deltoid, with the very top of the inverted triangle NOT being acceptable. My understanding is that the pain level from injecting at the rotator cuff is unnecessary and can lead to SIRVA - "Shoulder Injury from Vaccine." Please take the necessary steps to ensure the vaccine is being properly administered at the correct place in the arm. Otherwise, too many people will be undergoing unnecessary, extreme pain as I have .

Bloodwork was obtained by PCP which had revealed eosinophilia (AEC peaked 4250) without evidence of end organ damage. He underwent skin biopsy which revealed: Superficial and mid dermal perivascular infiltrate. Additionally, there are focal interface changes where lymphocytes approximate the dermal-epidermal junction and are associated with vacuolar alteration. A few eosinophils are noted in the infiltrate but they are not numerous. Vasculitis is not seen. These histologic features are not entirely specific, but are most suggestive of a hypersensitivity reaction. Initially treated with topical steroids. When eosinophil count was noted to be above 4,000 the patient was started on 60 mg of prednisone daily (this was on 1/26/21) and repeat CBC with differential are pending. The rash is improving and fever curve is also improving (on tylenol q8H PRN). He was referred to hematology/oncology for consideration of bone marrow biopsy, as hypereosinophilic syndrome is also on differential diagnosis.

69 2021-03-09 injection site pain, injection site hardening Because of the absurd character limit in this field, I am putting my adverse reaction statement on t... Read more
Close
Because of the absurd character limit in this field, I am putting my adverse reaction statement on the continuation page. About 10pm, about 9 hours post injection, I was feeling weak and fatigued. I went to bed and was starting to feel chilled, but not shaking. I hopped into bed and turned on my electric blanket in a room that was 75° (from passive solar house heating during the day) and wearing only a T-shirt, sweat shirt, and sweat pants. The first post-vaccination symptom I experienced was when I laid down and my right upper arm (at the point of the injection) was very sore; it was too painful to lie on my right side. The injection area felt hard. I fell asleep about 11pm and woke up about midnight; I am generally a very light sleeper, rarely sleeping more than ~3± hours (most less than) at a time. At 1:30am, I could not sleep so I watched a recorded movie. All the while, I was feeling progressively worse. About 2:30am, I felt really chilled, so I cranked up the electric blanket to its highest setting and put on some heavy wool socks, a pair of long-johns under my sweat pants, put on another heavy sweatshirt over my existing sweatshirt, and placed another blanket on top of my electric blanket: very cold / chilled but not shivering. The movie ended about 3am, and my stomach was excruciatingly aching. I did not feel I could eat anything which I really felt a need to do, but was concerned that I would just vomit. However, I did take two, 500mg Tylenol tablets with a half a glass of water. I might have slept for an hour or so, but was quite restless. I remember looking at the clock at 4:00am. By 5am, it was considering calling 911; my stomach ached so badly. It was then, that I had the feeling / recollection I had this "illness" before. About 5:30am, my stomach symptoms started to ameliorate; by 7:30am, they were gone. However, I still felt miserable. I then wondered whether my stomach symptom was just a concomitant bout with "stomach flu" where I experienced (severe) abdominal cramps and pain; nausea; and low-grade fever. I have had the stomach flu a limited number of times before and, after 6± hours, it all went away: I just had to suck it up in the meantime. Before I filled out this report, I wanted to consider whether my stomach flu was a reaction to the vaccination or incidental to the vaccination. However, after talking with my neighbors and my sister's friend, who also had the Moderna vaccination, three of the four "victims" had similar symptoms to me. Thus, I deduced I did not have a bout with stomach flu. Additionally, a dog walking partner, who is a rescue worker, also noted folks she knew also had similar symptoms with the Moderna vaccine. I then started wondering what kind of artificial cocktail, a.k.a.: antifreeze, was the suspending medium for the vaccine. If this has to be stored at absurdly low temperatures I commonly have negative reactions to artificial chemicals. The minor surgeries I have had are uneventful but for the anesthesia chemical concoction I am given. I commonly takes me more then 2-3 days to detoxify that and feel normal.' As in this case, I pretty much laid in bed for the next 2½ days, with no energy or desire to attend to personal issues, including walking my dogs. However, my subclinical temperature was pretty much gone after the second day. The notable soreness in my arm was mostly gone after two days, but the injection point was still sensitive to pressing on top of the injection site: I could still feel it. I have a very high tolerance for pain and have never experienced anything like this. "Pain" from flu, etc., shots rarely, if ever, lasts more than 10-15 minutes post injection. There was definitely something in the suspension media that reacted with my body chemistry / biological processes. I am NOT looking forward to the booster shot; most seem to have a reaction to the second shot that is worse than the first  unless their first shot was uneventful and the second shot had considerably milder reactions than my first shot. The next time I will definitely have a bowl or two of jell-O in the refrigerator to help quell any (expected) gut reactions; jell-O has always been a comfort food for me in those situations. What a horribly designed survey. This is next to impossible to complete online. After timing out twice, I had to start over and opted to download the fillable form PDF. Even then, I am not given the option to select the subdirectory _where_ it should be downloaded. Fortunately, I saw the option to open it directly. If you are going to make the "adverse reaction" field so limited, relative to field size and the absurd online time limit, how can you expect meaningful, complete reporting of post-vaccination reactions? This form CANNOT be fully completed in the time allotted without timing out. This is, most certainly, a deterrent to adverse reaction reporting. One has to wonder how many folks just gave up after getting timed out the first time. With this kind of disincentive, how good or complete or meaningful is the adverse data collection procedure? Have you purged all the supporters? They do not like real, accurate, objective data, particularly information that is not consistent what they want to believe or the narrative they want to spin. No respectable scientist or decent journalist would accept third-rate data. How can public interest decisions be made with a shoddy data collection effort?

The patient's medical history was not provided. No relevant concomitant medications were reported. On 01 Feb 2021, at 13:30, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 012MZ0A/012M20A) intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 01 Feb 2021, during vaccine administration, the syringe separated from the needle and leaked onto the patient's skin. It wasn't clear if the full dose was given. The pharmacist administering the vaccine then tried to give a second dose and the same thing happened both times. The patient was not sure how much he received. No treatment was provided. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported. The events of "the syringe separated from the needle and leaked out on my skin", and "the pharmacist who administered the vaccine tried twice in giving the dose and same thing happen both times; don't know how much I got", were considered resolved on 01 Feb 2021. The event outcome of "I had a little tenderness, no pain" was considered unknown.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. Very limited information regarding these event/s has been provided at this time

Ringing in left ear; Hearing loss in right ear; Ear ringing in right ear; Mild soreness at the site of injection; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer, a 71 year-old male patient, who received Moderna's COVID-19 Vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced hearing loss in right ear/deafness unilateral, ear ringing in right ear/tinnitus, ringing in left ear/tinnitus, and mild soreness at the site of injection/injection site pain. The patient's medical history included a kidney transplant. Concomitant product use was not provided. On 19 Jan 2021, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received the first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number: 029L20A) in the left arm for COVID-19 infection prophylaxis. The patient had some mild soreness at the site of the injection which lasted one to two days. On 21 Jan 2021, he experienced some ear ringing in his right ear which was followed by hearing loss that lasted six hours. Both the ear ringing and hearing loss resolved by the next morning. On 24 Jan 2021, the patient had ringing in his left ear, but it was not associated with hearing loss. The patient stated he thinks the tromethamine hydrochloride in the vaccine may have induced his hearing loss. Treatment information was not provided. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not provided. The events, hearing loss in right ear and ear ringing in right ear, were considered resolved on 22 Jan 2021. The event, mild soreness at the site of injection, was considered resolved on an unknown date Jan 2021. The outcome for the event, ringing in left ear, was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 71- year old male patient who experienced hearing loss in right ear/deafness unilateral, ear ringing in right ear/tinnitus, ringing in left ear/tinnitus, and mild soreness at the site of injection/injection site pain, all within 4 days after administration of Moderna's COVID-19 Vaccine (mRNA-1273). Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

Patient received first dose of COVID-19 Moderna vaccine on 1/28/2020. Due to his history of allergies and asthma, he took a dose of diphenhydramine 25mg (either 1 tablet or 2 tablet - patient is unsure) prior to receiving the first dose of the vaccine. He waiting for 30 minutes of observation afterwards. He did not have any problems other than a sore arm after the dose. The patient returned for his second dose of the COVID-19 Moderna vaccine on 2/25/2020. He forgot to take a dose of diphenhydramine prior to coming in for his second dose of the vaccine. He sat for the 30 minutes of observation with no issues. He drove home and after arriving home, 1 hour after receiving the dose, he started having a strange feeling around his mouth and tongue which moved from the right to left side. He then took two doses of diphenhydramine 25 mg. Then he started having difficulty swallowing so went to a Prompt Care. The staff there called an ambulance and he took an ambulance. In the ED, the physicians examined him and didn't find any issues with his throat. They noticed his left earlobe was bright red. They administered a high dose of steroid and observed him for 3 hours. The patient does not know the name of the steroid or dose received. The patient states that he felt normal again after 1.5 hours after receiving the steroid injection. The patient was discharged back home and has not had any issues since.

URINARY TRACT INFECTION; pink in my urine; Little bit of Pain after injection in left arm; A spontaneous report was received from a 71 years old, male patient, who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced urinary tract infection (urinary tract infection), pink in my urine (chromaturia) and little bit of pain in arm of injection (pain in extremity). The patient's medical history was not provided. The relevant concomitant medications were also not provided. On 02 Feb 2021, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA (Lot number:013M20A ) through intramuscular route of administration in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 02 Feb 2021, patient experienced little bit of pain in arm of injection. On 23 Feb 2021, patient experienced pink in urine. The patient subsequently visited the urgent care on 26-Feb-2021 and was diagnosed with a urinary tract infection. Treatment for urinary tract infection included ciprofloxacin 500 mg twice daily for 7days. No laboratory data was provided. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported. The event little bit of pain in arm of injection was resolved 03 Feb 2021. The event pink in urine was resolved on 01 Mar 2021. The outcome of the event urinary tract infection was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event (vaccination site pain) a causal relationship cannot be excluded. However, for the events - chromaturia and UTI, a very limited information has been provided at this time. Further information has been requested.

71 2021-03-22 itchy skin, blister I visited my doctor. After he examined and questioned me about recent activities, he diagnosed me w... Read more
Close
I visited my doctor. After he examined and questioned me about recent activities, he diagnosed me with a Stevens-Johnson response and said that my shot of the Moderna vaccine was the most likely cause of the incident. Much of my body was covered with red blisters and inflammation. It was uncomfortable and itched a lot. He prescribed a six-day course of methylprednisolone tablets for me, 21 - 4mg tablets over six days. That seemed to stop the reaction, but I still had badly inflamed hands and feet afterward. My doctor then prescribed prednisone, 1 - 10mg tablet per day. After another week, the inflammation was gone and I discontinued the prednisone.

71 2021-03-26 cellulitis, redness I spoke on 03/09/2021 with a question from him. He received his first dose of COVID-19 vaccine as Mo... Read more
Close
I spoke on 03/09/2021 with a question from him. He received his first dose of COVID-19 vaccine as Moderna on 02/16/2021. He reports he did well with his shot initially and didn't really even have a sore arm. About 6-7 days after his vaccine, however, he started getting some significant redness, warmth, tenderness and then swelling in his arm that continued to worsen. became concerned that his reaction was more than would be normally expected so he was seen by a doctor who diagnosed him with cellulitis and started him on antibiotics and steroids. He had completed his antibiotics at the time of our conversation and said his arm felt better but was still slightly red. His doctor recommended that he not get a second dose of Moderna, but suggested that he might get a Pfizer or a Janssen vaccine instead, and was wondering about our recommendation for this? I let patient know that there are no specific studies for the interchangability of these vaccines but there is a statement from CDC that says if an individual is unable to get a 2nd dose of an mRNA vaccine due to a contraindication, they could consider getting one dose of Janssen vaccine at least 28 days after the first dose to have a complete valid J&J dose. I encouraged to speak with his provider about this possibility and any further action. I did some education on potential causes of cellulitis and let him know that per immunization guidance, cellulitis isn't necessarily a contraindication to a second dose of vaccine but more of a precaution as it can be difficult to know the exact cause and a second dose may not result in the same side effect. Several times reported no respiratory symptoms or other symptoms than the cellulitis. I again recommended him to speak with his provider for the best plan of action and he agreed to this.

left side of face drooped; Chills; Mild Sore left arm; This spontaneous case was reported by a consumer and describes the occurrence of FACIAL PARALYSIS (left side of face drooped) in a 71-year-old male patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. The patient's past medical history included No adverse event (No reported medical history). On 06-Mar-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 06-Mar-2021, the patient experienced PAIN IN EXTREMITY (Mild Sore left arm). On 03-Apr-2021, the patient experienced FACIAL PARALYSIS (left side of face drooped) (seriousness criterion medically significant) and CHILLS (Chills). On 04-Apr-2021, CHILLS (Chills) had resolved. At the time of the report, FACIAL PARALYSIS (left side of face drooped) and PAIN IN EXTREMITY (Mild Sore left arm) outcome was unknown. The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) was unknown. No treatment information was reported. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. On 12-Feb-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 12-Mar-2021, received second dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) dosage was changed to 1 dosage form. On 14-Feb-2021, the patient experienced RASH (Small specks on face and chest and body). On 12-Mar-2021, the patient experienced IMMUNE THROMBOCYTOPENIA (Immune Thrombocytopenia diagnosed by hospital) (seriousness criteria hospitalization and medically significant) and AUTOIMMUNE HAEMOLYTIC ANAEMIA (Autoimmune hemolytic anemia diagnosed by hospital) (seriousness criterion hospitalization). The patient was hospitalized for 13 days due to AUTOIMMUNE HAEMOLYTIC ANAEMIA and IMMUNE THROMBOCYTOPENIA. At the time of the report, IMMUNE THROMBOCYTOPENIA (Immune Thrombocytopenia diagnosed by hospital), AUTOIMMUNE HAEMOLYTIC ANAEMIA (Autoimmune hemolytic anemia diagnosed by hospital) and RASH (Small specks on face and chest and body) outcome was unknown. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter. Wife on behalf of husband reported serious adverse effects after getting both the shots. After the 1st shot he developed little specks on face and chest. After his second shot on 12 Mar 2021, lot no 031A22A a day after the shot specks appeared again but this time they multiplied in thousands. He was hospitalized because of this for 13 days and doctors diagnosed him with ITP Immune thrombocytopenia. He has a complete platelet drop and his platelets numbers dropped to 1000. He had multiple platelet infusions and developed Autoimmune hemolytic anemia all because of this shot. He had no underline condition and was not taking any medication at the time of shot. Treatment medications was not provided. Company comment:Very limited information regarding this events has been provided at this time. Further information has been requested. Summary of ED physician assessment from 1/2/21 Medical Decision Making Patient seen by me on: 1/2/2021 Assessment: 72 year old male presenting with right sided facial weakness. No paralysis on exam but mildly notably weaker on R side. Otherwise, neurologically intact on exam. Differential diagnosis: Bell's Palsy, Incomplete Bell's Palsy, CNS lesion, vaccine adverse effect, lymphadenopathy Considered CVA, not a TPA candidate based on timing and minor deficits. May need to obtain MRI to evaluate. Plan: EKG, basic labs Discussed with patient, who is a physician, given risk factors and not classic Bell's Palsy, will proceed with MRI brain. ED Course and Disposition: MRI unremarkable. I feel this adequately rules out stroke and CNS lesion as a cause of facial weakness. CBC, CMP unremarkable. Patient's exam remains stable. We discussed risks/benefits of steroids. Concerns being his diabetes as well as blunting immune response to vaccine. He has mild facial asymmetry but not complete and will hold off on steroids unless worsening symptoms. COVID testing sent as discussed with patient. He will return to ED or see PCP if symptoms worsen. Dx- Bell's Palsy 01/02/21 1231

This increased over the next few hours and by the next morning my lower forearm was involved. The surgical site was about 2 inches long, stitches had been removed ten days before and the wound was mostly healed. The rash extended from the wound site toward the wrist about 2 inches, radiated laterally along the length of the wound about 2 inches on either side and up into the upper forearm another 3 inches. There were small blisters within the rash as well. I initially tried a cortisone cream I had left over from a previous wound. This seemed to inflame the rash even more and I stopped. I then applied some of the antibiotic cream I used when the wound was fresh and actively treated. This seemed to reduce the inflammation some. After 2 days I contacted my dermatologist who prescribed Triamcinolone Acetonide 0.1 % External Cream. I have been taking this for 24 hours, 3 applications and the rash is beginning to dissipate. My dermatologist indicated I was the third patient to have a rash on the same arm with a surgery and a Moderna shot, in the same arm.

Close
Awakened from sound sleep in morning of January 6th (~8 days post vaccination) with intense pruritis (itching) of left shoulder and arm (injection site and bicep region). When I arose in the morning, I noticed a wide (approximately 3-inch band) of erythema (redness) extending from injection site in left shoulder and extending along outer aspect of bicep to about 2 inches above antecubital fossa (bend of elbow). I applied roll-on topical anesthetic (4% lidocaine) and 1% hydrocortisone cream, which diminished but did not completely eliminate the itching. Last night, I added OTC Benadryl 25 mg orally, 1 dose. Today, itching is less, but still present. On upper left arm and shoulder the erythema is slightly less, while redness is more intense, but sharply demarcated at the base of the bicep (about 1 inch above the elbow crease. Seems likely this is a delayed allergic reaction. Unless instructed otherwise, will likely not proceed with second dose of vaccine.

73 2021-01-29 skin discolouration, injection site pain MY REACTION TO THE FIRST DOSE: In March of 2020 I suffered Covid pneumonia and was on oxygen and too... Read more
Close
MY REACTION TO THE FIRST DOSE: In March of 2020 I suffered Covid pneumonia and was on oxygen and too weak and short of breath to work for three months. It took over seven months to return my breathing and strength to baseline. I just checked my lab and I still have IgG antibodies and a negative nasal screen for the virus. One month ago at 9 AM I received the Moderna Vaccine. About 12 hours later I developed shaking chills and a fever of about 103, pain in my arm from the injection, and severe cough and a VERY WATERY RUNNY NOSE with severe post nasal drip which caused aspiration of the discharge. I took Tylenol, Afrin Nasal Spray, and a Dulera inhaler and fell asleep. I woke up at 3 AM and felt well, but at 4 AM I developed an intolerable intractable cough and severe watery nasal discharge lasting about two hours and severe dry heaves from the aspiration. Afrin nasal spray helped somewhat but I was absolutely miserable for two hours. Three days ago I received the one month booster for the Moderna Vaccine at 10AM. My arm began to become painful but it was tolerable and not relieved by Tylenol. Every time I rolled over at night the pain woke me up but I was able to tolerate it. Yesterday I woke up with severe constant chills but my temperature was normal. I felt very hungry and diaphoretic and felt like I had a low blood sugar, and ate a bowl of rice chex cereal. I felt a little better but a half hour later VOMITED everything up. I then felt somewhat better and went to the hospital to make rounds. The nursing staff reported that about half of them called in sick due to the vaccine with severe fatigue, fever, joint pains and headaches. One nurse reported that all her joints felt like they were on fire. Four nursing supervisors also called in sick that day. I then went to my office and my staff said I looked GREEN and insisted I go home. I did not eat anything but while resting I again had SEVERE VOMITING of my breakfast at about noon. When I felt stronger I drove home at about 1:30 PM and fell asleep until about 5 PM, still not having eaten anything nor taking fluids. My arm pain went away. By 7 PM I finally drank some tea and felt stronger and felt like I was not going to die. It seems that those of use who had the Covid in the past do not tolerate the vaccine and suffer severe reactions. I was unable to find any studies with the vaccine given to patients who already have antibodies. This lack of data is a real problem.

On January 19, 2021 (4 days after the vaccine injection) I developed severe itching in the palms of my hands. By the next day, January 20, 2021, I had developed severe hives bilaterally from my groin areas down to almost my knees, as well as on my buttox. I also had severe hives in both armpits. Both hands (palms) and wrists had become swollen and fire-engine red and the itching was maddening. I saw a Physician who gave me an injection of Depo Medrol and a 7 day prescription of Dexamethasone, 4mg , take twice a day and a prescription of Hydroxyzine HCL 25 mg, 4 times a day as needed. The hives began to fade after 18 hours of medication and got fainter and fainter each day, along with relief from itching. Hives were completely gone by the time I completed the 7 day cycle of Dexamethasone. I have not had a recurrence.

Rash from elbow to armpit all the way to the back; Vertigo; Nausea/vomiting; Tired/ could not make 2 steps; Nausea, vomiting; This spontaneous case was reported by a consumer (subsequently medically confirmed) and describes the occurrence of RASH (Rash from elbow to armpit all the way to the back) and VERTIGO (Vertigo) in a 75-year-old male patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch nos. 002A21A and 016821A) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. No medical history reported by the reporter. Concomitant products included ATORVASTATIN, DABIGATRAN ETEXILATE MESILATE (PRADAXA) and METFORMIN for an unknown indication. On 26-Feb-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 26-Mar-2021, received second dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) dosage was changed to 1 dosage form. On an unknown date, the patient experienced RASH (Rash from elbow to armpit all the way to the back) (seriousness criterion medically significant), VERTIGO (Vertigo) (seriousness criterion medically significant), VOMITING (Nausea/vomiting), FATIGUE (Tired/ could not make 2 steps) and NAUSEA (Nausea, vomiting). At the time of the report, RASH (Rash from elbow to armpit all the way to the back), VERTIGO (Vertigo), VOMITING (Nausea/vomiting), FATIGUE (Tired/ could not make 2 steps) and NAUSEA (Nausea, vomiting) outcome was unknown. The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) was unknown. The patent stated that 6 to 10 days after the administration of the second vaccine the patient started to develop a rash from his elbow to his armpit, then the next day the rash was all the way to his back. Patient also experienced nausea, vomiting and vertigo. The patient went to the emergency room on 21-APR-2021 and was prescribed prednisone, ibuprofen, loratadine. Company comment: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.; Sender's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.
